<TITLE> Three economic ministers appointed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 29 (bdnews24.com)--The government appointed on Thursday economic ministers to diplomatic missions in the US, Japan, and Saudi Arabia. The establishment ministry announced their appointments in separate orders. Additional secretary, an officer on special duty at the establishment ministry, Wahid Hossain has been made the economic minister in Bangladesh embassy in Washington. Additional secretary AKM Manjurul Haque, who was the director general of the Export Promotion Bureau, will join as economic minister in the Tokyo mission. Deputy secretary-level official Dr Mizanur Rahman, who was a deputy director at the Regional Public Administration Centre in Dhaka, was made the economic minister in Riyadh. The government also appointed retired additional secretary Abdur Rab Khan, on contract, to the Bangladesh Institute of Management as director general
